There are some properties in CSS that are NOT inherited.
Example : box-sizing.
* selector is a way to apply such properties to elements.
*{
	box-sizing:border-box;
}

This selector will select all the elments in the HTML document and apply the properties 
in the rule to each one of them. 


Margin:
Margins on the sides are cumulative
Margins on the top and bottom collapse to the maximum value from the specified top/bottom margins